author: Inside Edition
description: Bryan Kobel says an Uber driver refused to take his service dog and attacked him. The driver reportedly told cops he's allergic to dogs. Kobel is now suing the driver and Uber claiming the driver "was not legally in the United States" and his license “was fake.” The driver's lawyer says his license is legit and “the video doesn't tell the full story.” Uber says while it can't comment on pending litigation, it is “deeply committed to safety” and” there is no place for violence” on its platform.
title: Passenger Says He Was Headbutted by Uber Driver Over Service Dog

author: Inside Edition
description: Donna Adelson is accused of orchestrating the murder of her daughter's estranged husband, Dan Markel. Her daughter, Wendi Adelson, wanted to move to South Carolina to be close to her mother with her two young sons. Prosecutors say Markel wanted them to stay in Tallahassee, Florida which led to his assassination. Prosecutors are painting Donna as a mother controlling her daughter's life. Wendi took to the stand Monday. She has denied any involvement in Markel's death.
title: Wendi Adelson Takes Stand in Her Mother's Murder Trial

author: Inside Edition
description: Tami Laird was driving her 9-year-old son Stirling to Cub Scout Camp when their GPS took them off road onto a rugged trail. Their car bottomed out and they were left stranded in the wilderness. Tami wrote a series of notes and placed them on surrounding trails, hoping someone would look for them as they remained lost in California's Sierra Nevada. A search and rescue team discovered them 24 hours later after discovering the notes.
title: Mom and Son Lead Rescuers to Their Location with Handwritten Notes

author: Inside Edition
description: A prayer with his family, it's the last thing Kilmar Abrego Garcia did before he went to a scheduled ICE check-in appointment in Baltimore and was arrested. Abrego Garcia became a symbol of the Trump administration's hard stance on immigration earlier this year. He was mistakenly deported to El Salvador in March, and a lengthy legal fight ensued to return him to the US. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Kilmar Abrego Garcia Arrested During ICE Check-in Appointment

author: Inside Edition
description: Barth Syndrome is a genetic disease so rare that fewer than 200 Americans have it, and there are under 300 known cases worldwide. It hinders the mitochondria in cells and affects the body from head to toe.
title: What Is Barth Syndrome? #shorts
